		<div class="comment-body"><p>Excellent show!</p>
<p>Here is more on trombe/trompe systems:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.motherearthnews.com/renewable-energy/hydro-power-zmaz77jazbon.aspx#axzz2KASqPrWg" rel="nofollow">http://www.motherearthnews.com/renewable-energy/hydro-power-zmaz77jazbon.aspx#axzz2KASqPrWg</a></p>
<p>They are traditionally sited near waterfalls, but if you have a slow means of pumping water from a well (e.g., wind pump or solarjack pump) to a high tank, a trombe can be used to create cool, dry air.</p>
