<a href="http://thesurvivalpodcast.com/forum/index.php?topic=40017" rel="nofollow">http://thesurvivalpodcast.com/forum/index.php?topic=40017</a></p>
<p>My wife and her brother, mom and sis-in-law visited the San Antonio and Austin area in early December. They drove all over the hill country. They stopped to take a picture of a &#8220;Don&#8217;t Mess with Texas&#8221; sign. A woman was hauling her groceries in from the car nearby. She came over and asked if they were OK, if they needed anything and if they wanted to come into her home and use the restroom. (What?) I live in a nice town 1hr North of Seattle where most people are polite&#8230;but there is no way that would happen around here.</p>
</div>

